[[Image:Explorer Ridge sulfide chimney.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Sulfide chimney of Magic Mountain]] '''Magic Mountain''' is a large long-lived [[hydrothermal vent]] field on the [[Explorer Ridge|Southern Explorer Ridge]], located about 150 miles west of [[Vancouver Island]], [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]]. Unlike most hydrothermal systems found in the [[Pacific Ocean]], Magic Mountain is situated outside the Explorer Ridge. Its source is believed to rise along [[fault (geology)|fault]] systems.<ref>[http://oceanexplorer.noaa.gov/explorations/02fire/logs/yr_sum/yr_sum.html NOAA Ocean Explorer: Submarine Ring of Fire] Retrieved on 2007-11-18</ref>
==See also== {{Portal|Volcanism of Canada}} *[[Volcanism of Canada]] *[[Volcanism of Western Canada]]
